CC   -!- FUNCTION: Plays a role in the differentiation or division of feeding
CC       cells (syncytia) induced in plant roots during infection. Promotes host
CC       root growth. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16985000}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000250}. Host cytoplasm
CC       {ECO:0000250}. Host extracellular space {ECO:0000250}. Note=Secreted
CC       into host root cells via the nematode stylet to transform the recipient
CC       cells into enlarged multinucleate feeding cells called giant-cells or
CC       syncytia. {ECO:0000250}.
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Highly expressed exclusively within the subventral
CC       esophageal gland cell during syncytium formation in host plants.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the CLV3/ESR signal peptide family.
CC       {ECO:0000305}.
