CC   -!- FUNCTION: Produces peripheral paralysis by blocking neuromuscular
CC       transmission at the postsynaptic site. Weak inhibitor of the endogenous
CC       nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (nAChR) in the human rhabdomyosarcoma
CC       TE 671 cell line with an IC(50) of 690 mM. This neurotoxin is lethal to
CC       zebrafish by injection at the back of the dorsolateral region, but is
CC       not toxic to mice by intraperitoneal injection.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18384102}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18384102}.
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Expressed by the venom gland. {ECO:0000305}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the three-finger toxin family. Ancestral
CC       subfamily. {ECO:0000305}.
