CC   -!- FUNCTION: Lectin which binds carbohydrates in vitro. Interacts through
CC       its lectin domain with glycan structures containing specific motifs.
CC       {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:Q945P1}.
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Expressed in shoots and lamina.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:9265787}.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: Induced by abscisic acid (ABA) and salt stress in shoots.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:9265787}.
CC   -!- DOMAIN: The ricin B-type lectin domain binds glycan structures.
CC       {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:Q945P1}.
