RA   Wainwright S.M., Hopkins B.R., Mendes C.C., Sekar A., Kroeger B.,
RA   Hellberg J.E.E.U., Fan S.J., Pavey A., Marie P.P., Leiblich A., Sepil I.,
RA   Charles P.D., Thezenas M.L., Fischer R., Kessler B.M., Gandy C.,
RA   Corrigan L., Patel R., Wigby S., Morris J.F., Goberdhan D.C.I., Wilson C.;
RT   "Drosophila Sex Peptide controls the assembly of lipid microcarriers in
RT   seminal fluid.";
RL   Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. 118:0-0(2021).
CC   -!- FUNCTION: Male seminal protein which triggers short- and long-term
CC       post-mating behavioral responses (PMR) in female Drosophila. Binds
CC       initially to sperm where it is later cleaved to release an active
CC       peptide within the female reproductive tract. Signals via the sex
CC       peptide receptor (SPR) in female flies; may also act via other
CC       receptors. Moderates the activity of distinct neuronal circuitries in
CC       the female genital tract to promote specific PMRs including: enhanced
CC       ovulation, increased egg laying rate, increased feeding/foraging rate,
CC       induced antimicrobial peptide synthesis, reduced mating receptivity,
CC       reduced day-time sleep and reduced lifespan in multiple mated females
CC       (By similarity). Structural component of large neutral lipid-containing
CC       microcarriers produced by male accessory gland main cells; involved in
CC       their morphogenesis and their role in delivering lipids and lipid
CC       associated proteins to females during mating (PubMed:33495334).
CC       {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623, ECO:0000269|PubMed:33495334}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623}.
CC       Note=Surface component of large neutral lipid-containing microcarriers
CC       produced by male accessory gland main cells and secreted into seminal
CC       fluid. Microcarriers disassembl in females after delivery by mating,
CC       and components including some SP protein associate with tails of stored
CC       sperm. {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623}.
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Main cells of the accessory glands of males
CC       (paragonial gland). {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623}.
CC   -!- DOMAIN: The N-terminal domain is important for microcarrier assembly as
CC       well as sperm binding. {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623}.
CC   -!- PTM: Sperm-bound protein is cleaved to release an active C-terminal
CC       peptide. Gradual release from stored sperm may function to prolong PMR
CC       and enhance male reproductive success. {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P05623}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the Drosophila sex peptide family.
CC       {ECO:0000305}.
